            <title>[JDK-8312498] Thread::getState and JVM TI GetThreadState should return TIMED_WAITING virtual thread is timed parked</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8312498</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>If a virtual thread is in a timed-parked (LockSupport.parkNanos) then Thread::getThread returns WAITING rather than TIMED_WAITING. The Thread::getState method was added for monitoring and management purposes but should be fixed.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
JVM TI GetThreadState has a similar issue. It returns the state with the JVMTI_THREAD_STATE_WAITING_INDEFINITELY rather than JVMTI_THREAD_STATE_WAITING_WITH_TIMEOUT bit set.</description>
